sub_unit.name: Chatham
sub_unit.note: James Sullivan received 25 votes as James Solvan.

sub_unit.name: Harrison
sub_unit.note: There were no votes recorded in Harrison.

Harrison was organized March 18, 1805 and the first Town meeting took place on August 26, 1805. State elections took place on April 1, 1805 and Harrison probably voted with one of the towns from which it was separated.
